Johannesburg police say New Year celebrations in the city were marred by several deaths. Two deaths occurred in Hillbrow and one in Mary Fitzgerald square. No one has been arrested in connection with the incidents. Police spokesperson, Kay Makhubele says, “A security guard who was entering his place of work in a hotel in Hillbrow was shot and killed. We also had one incident in Marry Fitzgerald Square where there was a concert. A person was found stabbed. He died at the scene. We had another incident where a person fell from the flat in Hillbrow.” Watch related videos below